citeinfo.title: Canoe Routes for Major Rivers in The State of Iowa

descript.purpose: This digital, geographically referenced data set was developed by the Iowa Department of Natural Resources to carry out agency responsibilities related to management, protection, and development of Iowa's natural resources.
descript.abstract: This file represents canoe route segments for major rivers in the state of Iowa.

idinfo.useconst: The development of the coverages in the NRGIS Library represents a major investment of staff time and effort. As a professional responsibility, the Iowa DNR expects to receive proper credit when these GIS coverages are utilized. The Department also expects that the original documentation will remain with any redistribution of these coverages.

horizpa.horizpar: River segments should be accurate to 20 meters

procstep.procdesc: Segments were drawn out of the GAP_nhd_streams shapefile. These were then moved to run along the river using Color Infrared (CIR) photgraphy. Segments were then merged to one then split at access points. The length in miles was then calculated using XTools.

attracc.attraccr: River segments were digitized using Color Infrared (CIR) photgraphy.

dataqual.complete: This dataset is complete as of the points entered for Fishing and Boating Access points.
